# Subscription Constraints Implementation Plan

## Analysis Summary

After analyzing the reference `Frontend.zip` and comparing with the current project, here are all the subscription-based constraints that need to be applied:

## 1. TryOnPage — MISSING constraints
- [ ] Block try-on when `is_subscription_expired === true`
- [ ] Check `remaining_tryons_today <= 0` → show upgrade modal
- [ ] Show expiry warning message below the submit button
- [ ] Show "Upgrade Required" modal with plan-specific messages

## 2. RecommendationsPage — PARTIALLY done
- [ ] Disable "Get Recommendations" button when `is_subscription_expired`
- [ ] Show toast warning on page load when subscription expired
- [ ] **Occasion filter plan-gating**: Only Standard/Premium plans get occasion filter; Basic shows disabled dropdown
- [ ] Show "Upgrade Required" modal when daily limit reached

## 3. WardrobeManagementPage — MISSING constraints
- [ ] Add Activate/Deactivate toggle per item (API exists: `PATCH /wardrobe/items/{id}/status`)
- [ ] Show active/inactive status badge per item
- [ ] Visual opacity (0.7) for inactive items
- [ ] Show embedding status (ready/pending) per item
- [ ] Fetch items with `include_inactive=true`

## 4. SubscriptionPage — MISSING constraint
- [ ] **Downgrade blocking modal**: When purchasing a plan with lower `wardrobe_limit` than current wardrobe count, show modal saying "Remove extra items before downgrading"

## 5. Backend APIs — Already complete ✅
- `PATCH /wardrobe/items/{id}/status` — toggle active/inactive
- `ensure_wardrobe_capacity` — checks wardrobe limit
- `is_subscription_expired` flag — returned in user profile
- `remaining_tryons_today` / `remaining_recommendations_today` — returned in profile
